/-! ## 1. Convergence of Squarefree Divisor Sums for `k ‚â• 3`

For `k ‚â• 3` and `Œµ > 0`, the exponent `k - 2 + Œµ ‚â• 1 + Œµ > 1`, so the p-series
`‚àë_{n ‚â• 1} n^{-(k-2+Œµ)}` converges. Since every squarefree divisor of `q` is a
